<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EEC) No 1323/86 of 5 May 1986 amending Regulation (EEC) No 1351/72 on the recognition of producer groups for hops </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 1323/86, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1351/72 tootjar&uuml;hmade tunnustamise kohta humalasektoris 5. mai 1986 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1696/7 of 26 July 1971 on the common organization of the market in hops (1), as last amended by Council Regulation (EEC) No 3800/85 of 31 December 1985 (2), and in particular Article 7 (5) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 26. juuli 1971. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1696/71 humalaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) viimati muudetud n&otilde;ukogu 31. detsembri 1985. aasta m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 3800/85, (2) eriti selle artikli 7 l&otilde;iget 5, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Council Regulation (EEC) No 3332/85 of 26 November 1985 amending Regulation (EEC) No 1696/71 on the common organization of the market in hops (3) amended Article 7 of the latter in such a way as to permit producer groups to use aid to take not only measures leading to a greater concentration of supply and greater market stability by marketing the entire production of their members but also measures by means of which production can be improved and adapted to the requirements of the market; whereas Commission Regulation (EEC) No 1351/72 (4), containing the rules for the application of the said Article 7 should be adapted accordingly; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: n&otilde;ukogu 26. novembri 1985. aasta m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 3332/85, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1696/71 humalaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (3) on muudetud viimati nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruse artiklit 7 nii, et tootjar&uuml;hmadel on lubatud kasutada abi mitte ainult kogu oma liikmete toodangu turustamise kaudu pakkumise suuremat kontsentratsiooni ja turu suuremat stabiilsust edendavate meetmete heaks, vaid ka tootmise edendamise ja turun&otilde;uetele kohandamise meetmete heaks; komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1351/72, (4) milles on s&auml;testatud nimetatud artikli 7 rakenduseeskirjad, tuleks vastavalt kohandada; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Hops, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las humalaturu korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> In Article 1 (1) (b) (cc) the following is inserted after the words 'market stabilization measures': </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 1 l&otilde;ike 1 punkti b alapunktis cc lisatakse s&otilde;nade "turu tasakaalustamise meetmena" j&auml;rele j&auml;rgmine tekst: </eesti>
<inglise> 'as also for measures to improve and adapt production to market requirements'. </inglise>
<eesti> "ning tootmise edendamise ja turun&otilde;uetele kohandamise meetmena". </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 5 May 1986. </inglise>
